<p>I've created form in play framework with constraints: </p>  <pre><code>val voucherForm = Form(   mapping(     "voucherName" -&gt; nonEmptyText,     "voucherCode" -&gt; optional(text(minLength = 6).verifying(pattern("""[a-zA-Z0-9]+""".r, error = "...")))        )(VoucherForm.apply)(VoucherForm.unapply) ) </code></pre>  <p>when I display this form on a web page I have constraint messages (like <code>Required</code>, <code>Minimum length: 6, constraint.pattern</code>) shown near input boxes. </p>  <p>I want to customise this constraint messages per input field (i.e. two <code>nonEmptyText</code> constraints in same form will have different constraint message). How could I do it?</p>